            <title><![CDATA[Here's The GTA 6 Trailer Recreated In San Andreas]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-ps2-recreation-fan-san-andreas-ps5-1851781843</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/heres-the-gta-6-trailer-recreated-in-san-andreas.1195770/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-ps2-recreation-fan-san-andreas-ps5-1851781843<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><figure id="" data-id="87d9544f4d6401514dbe821c24de863e" data-recommend-id="image://87d9544f4d6401514dbe821c24de863e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="true" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Foosmoke / Rockstar Games / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="87d9544f4d6401514dbe821c24de863e" data-recommend-id="image://87d9544f4d6401514dbe821c24de863e" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="true" data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Someone has perfectly recreated the second <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-2-couple-jason-lucia-vice-city-trailer-2-1851779617&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-2-couple-jason-lucia-vice-city-trailer-2-1851779617"><em>Grand Theft Auto 6</em></a></span> trailer in the PS2-era <em>GTA </em>game <em>San Andrea</em>s (with some help from <em>Vice City,</em> too). </p><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><div data-video-id="196299" data-monetizable="true" data-position="sidebar" data-video-title="You Should Play Grand Theft Auto III Before GTA VI | Total Recall" data-video-blog-id="9" data-video-network="kotaku" data-video-duration="385" data-playlist="196299,197559,197554" data-current="196299"><div><p>You Should Play Grand Theft Auto III Before GTA VI | Total Recall</p></div><video disablepictureinpicture="" muted="" playsinline="" width="100%" height="100%" crossorigin="anonymous" preload="none"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196299/196299_240p.mp4" label="240p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196299/196299_480p.mp4" label="480p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196299/196299_720p.mp4" label="720p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/196299/196299_1080p.mp4" label="1080p" type="video/mp4"><track kind="captions" label="English" src="https://kinja.com/api/videoupload/caption/21849.vtt" srclang="en"></video><div><ul><li data-label="">Off</li><li data-label="English">English</li></ul></div></div><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><p>It’s a time-honored tradition to recreate new <em>Grand Theft Auto </em>trailers in older games and other media. And while it might not be a new phenomenon, it’s still enjoyable to watch these fan creations as they show us just how far Rockstar’s tech has come over the decades. So I knew that after Rockstar published <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-2-everything-spotted-round-up-easter-eggs-1851779329&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-2-everything-spotted-round-up-easter-eggs-1851779329"><em>GTA 6</em>'s second trailer earlier this month</a></span>, following the news that the open-world sequel was being delayed until May 2026, someone would set out to recreate the new video in a previous<em> GTA </em>game. And here we are. <br></p><p>Foosmoke made the video using mostly&nbsp;<em>GTA San Andreas</em> to recreate nearly every moment from the new <em>GTA 6</em> trailer. Sometimes the creator adds extra details using video editing tricks or bits from <em>Vice City,</em> but this is still more or less the <em>GTA 6</em> trailer recreated in <em>San Andreas</em>, and it’s a blast to watch. </p><p>Previously, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://youtu.be/_V1HzqpoAgU&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://youtu.be/_V1HzqpoAgU" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Foosmoke recreated the first <em>GTA 6</em> trailer</a></span> as if it were a PS2-era game. That video is also great. Of course, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-remakes-remix-lego-vice-city-san-andreas-1851157083&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-remakes-remix-lego-vice-city-san-andreas-1851157083">Foosmoke wasn’t alone in recreating that first trailer</a></span>. Plenty of people did as well, sometimes in other games or even, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-recreated-real-life-comparison-miami-1851240237?_gl=1*1vh7wqc*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDc4NTMyODMkbzg0JGcxJHQxNzQ3ODYxNjg3JGo1NyRsMCRoMCRkTGhKQ1VESkJYd2lqTzFUMTlocEx1a0ptWERkbVBiM21jZw..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/gta-6-trailer-recreated-real-life-comparison-miami-1851240237?_gl=1*1vh7wqc*_ga*MTc0MjY2NTg1OS4xNzQwMzc1OTc4*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDc4NTMyODMkbzg0JGcxJHQxNzQ3ODYxNjg3JGo1NyRsMCRoMCRkTGhKQ1VESkJYd2lqTzFUMTlocEx1a0ptWERkbVBiM21jZw..">in one case, in real life.</a></span> </p><p>Fans have done similar recreations in the past. I fondly remember this recreation of<em> </em><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://youtu.be/Vs75xPZSeH0&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://youtu.be/Vs75xPZSeH0" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Grand Theft Auto V</em>’s first trailer in <em>San Andreas</em></a></span>. It’s wild how much more realistic Rockstar’s newer <em>GTA </em>games look compared to past entries. However, I do miss the more primitive and blocky visuals, as they live firmly in a very nostalgic part of my brain. </p><p><em>Grand Theft Auto 6 </em>is set to launch on May 26, 2026, on PS5 and Xbox. </p><p> .<br></p></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
